        "body": "\n                    <h4>1. Intention (Niyyah)</h4>\n                    <p>Before beginning, you must make the intention for Wudu in your heart. You can also verbalize it:</p>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-arabic\">نَوَيْتُ أَنْ أَتَوَضَّأَ لِرَفْعِ الْحَدَثِ وَاسْتِبَاحَةِ الصَّلَاةِ تَقَرُّبًا إِلَى اللَّهِ تَعَالَى</div>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-pronunciation\">🔊 Nawaytu an atawadda'a li-raf'il-hadathi wa-istibāhatis-salāti taqarruban ilallāhi ta'ālā</div>\n                    <p>\"I intend to perform Wudu to remove impurity and to make prayer permissible, seeking nearness to Allah the Almighty.\"</p>\n                    <p><em>(Note: Until you learn the exact Arabic words for the Intention/Niyyah, simply making the firm intention in your heart and proceeding with Bismillah is completely valid and accepted.)</em></p>\n\n                    <h4>2. Starting with Bismillah</h4>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-arabic\">بِسْمِ اللّٰهِ</div>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-pronunciation\">🔊 Bismillah — \"In the name of Allah\"</div>\n                    \n                    <h4>3. Step-by-Step Actions</h4>\n                    <ol>\n                        <li><strong>Wash hands</strong> — three times, right then left, including between fingers.</li>\n                        <li><strong>Rinse mouth</strong> — three times, swishing water inside.</li>\n                        <li><strong>Sniff water into nostrils</strong> — gently inhale water into your nose and blow it out, three times.</li>\n                        <li><strong>Wash face</strong> — three times, from the forehead to the chin, and from ear to ear.</li>\n                        <li><strong>Wash forearms</strong> — three times each, including the elbows, starting with the right arm then the left.</li>\n                        <li><strong>Wipe head (Masah)</strong> — once, with wet hands, wipe from the front of the hair to the back and back to the front.</li>\n                        <li><strong>Wipe ears</strong> — once, using the index fingers for the inside and thumbs for the back of the ears.</li>\n                        <li><strong>Wash feet</strong> — three times each, up to and including the ankles, starting with the right foot then the left.</li>\n                    </ol>\n                    \n                    <h4>4. Dua After Wudu</h4>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-arabic\">أَشْهَدُ أَنْ لَا إِلٰهَ إِلَّا اللّٰهُ وَحْدَهُ لَا شَرِيكَ لَهُ وَأَشْهَدُ أَنَّ مُحَمَّدًا عَبْدُهُ وَرَسُولُهُ</div>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-pronunciation\">🔊 Ash-hadu an la ilaha illallahu wahdahu la sharika lahu, wa ash-hadu anna Muhammadan 'abduhu wa rasuluh</div>\n                    <p>\"I bear witness there is no god but Allah alone, with no partner, and Muhammad is His servant and Messenger.\" (Sahih Muslim 234)</p>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-arabic\">اللَّهُمَّ اجْعَلْنِي مِنَ التَّوَّابِينَ وَاجْعَلْنِي مِنَ الْمُتَطَهِّرِينَ</div>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-pronunciation\">🔊 Allahumm-aj'alni minat-tawwabina waj'alni minal-mutatahhireen</div>\n                    <p>\"O Allah, make me among those who repent and purify themselves.\" (Tirmidhi 55)</p>\n                ",
