        "body": "<h4>The Theology and Articulation of Niyyah (Intention)</h4>\n<p>In Islamic jurisprudence, the intention, universally known as the Niyyah, is the vital psychological and spiritual mechanism that separates a mundane daily action from an act of divine worship. The Niyyah is fundamentally an act of the heart and mind; knowing precisely which prayer is being offered, its specific timing, and its exact Rakat (unit) count is technically sufficient to fulfill the requirement. If a person stands with the clear mental recognition that they are about to perform the four obligatory Rakats of the Dhuhr prayer, the Niyyah is achieved.</p>\n<p>However, vocalizing the intention has become a widely accepted and highly recommended practice to assist beginners in cementing their focus and eliminating distracting thoughts before speaking to the Divine. The structural formula for a verbal Niyyah generally dictates the type of prayer (Fard, Sunnah, Nafl), the specific time of day (Fajr, Dhuhr, Asr, Maghrib, or Isha), the exact number of Rakats, and the physical direction of the Qiblah.</p>\n<p>To guide an unaware first-timer, the following table exhaustively catalogs the precise verbal Niyyahs for the various daily prayers and their specific combinations. If a worshipper is praying behind an Imam in a congregation, they must silently append the phrase \"I follow this Imam\" (e.g., eqtadaitu bihāzal imāmi) to their intention.</p>\n<div style=\"overflow-x:auto;\"><table class=\"salah-table\"><thead><tr><th>Salah Time</th><th>Prayer Type & Rakat Count</th><th>Transliterated Arabic Niyyah</th><th>English Translation</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>Fajr</td><td>2 Rakat Sunnah</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillāhi ta'ālā rak'atai salātil Fajr sunnatu rasūlillāhi ta'ālā mutawajjihan ilā jihatil ka'batish sharīfati, Allāhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 2 units of Fajr Sunnah, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Fajr</td><td>2 Rakat Fard</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillāhi ta'ālā rak'atai salātil Fajr fardullāhi ta'ālā mutawajjihan ilā jihatil ka'batish sharīfati, Allāhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 2 units of Fajr Fard (Obligatory), facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Dhuhr</td><td>4 Rakat Sunnah</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillāhi ta'ālā arba'a rak'āti salātiz Zuhr sunnatu rasūlillāhi ta'ālā mutawajjihan ilā jihatil ka'batish sharīfati, Allāhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 4 units of Dhuhr Sunnah, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Dhuhr</td><td>4 Rakat Fard</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillāhi ta'ālā arba'a rak'āti salātiz Zuhr fardullāhi ta'ālā mutawajjihan ilā jihatil ka'batish sharīfati, Allāhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 4 units of Dhuhr Fard, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Dhuhr</td><td>2 Rakat Sunnah</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillāhi ta'ālā rak'atai salātiz Zuhr sunnatu rasūlillāhi ta'ālā mutawajjihan ilā jihatil ka'batish sharīfati, Allāhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 2 units of Dhuhr Sunnah, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Dhuhr</td><td>2 Rakat Nafl</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillāhi ta'ālā rak'atai salātiz Zuhr nafli mutawajjihan ilā jihatil ka'batish sharīfati, Allāhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 2 units of Dhuhr Nafl (Voluntary), facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Asr</td><td>4 Rakat Sunnah</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillāhi ta'ālā arba'a rak'āti salātil Asr sunnatu rasūlillāhi ta'ālā mutawajjihan ilā jihatil ka'batish sharīfati, Allāhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 4 units of Asr Sunnah, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Asr</td><td>4 Rakat Fard</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillāhi ta'ālā arba'a rak'āti salātil Asr fardullāhi ta'ālā mutawajjihan ilā jihatil ka'batish sharīfati, Allāhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 4 units of Asr Fard, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Maghrib</td><td>3 Rakat Fard</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillāhi ta'ālā thalātha rak'āti salātil Maghrib fardullāhi ta'ālā mutawajjihan ilā jihatil ka'batish sharīfati, Allāhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 3 units of Maghrib Fard, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Maghrib</td><td>2 Rakat Sunnah</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillāhi ta'ālā rak'atai salātil Maghrib sunnatu rasūlillāhi ta'ālā mutawajjihan ilā jihatil ka'batish sharīfati, Allāhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 2 units of Maghrib Sunnah, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Maghrib</td><td>2 Rakat Nafl</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillāhi ta'ālā rak'atai salātil Maghrib nafli mutawajjihan ilā jihatil ka'batish sharīfati, Allāhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 2 units of Maghrib Nafl, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Isha</td><td>4 Rakat Sunnah</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillāhi ta'ālā arba'a rak'āti salātil Ishā' sunnatu rasūlillāhi ta'ālā mutawajjihan ilā jihatil ka'batish sharīfati, Allāhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 4 units of Isha Sunnah, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Isha</td><td>4 Rakat Fard</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillāhi ta'ālā arba'a rak'āti salātil Ishā' fardullāhi ta'ālā mutawajjihan ilā jihatil ka'batish sharīfati, Allāhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 4 units of Isha Fard, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Isha</td><td>2 Rakat Sunnah</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillāhi ta'ālā rak'atai salātil Ishā' sunnatu rasūlillāhi ta'ālā mutawajjihan ilā jihatil ka'batish sharīfati, Allāhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 2 units of Isha Sunnah, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Isha</td><td>3 Rakat Witr</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillāhi ta'ālā thalātha rak'āti salātil Witri wājibullāhi ta'ālā mutawajjihan ilā jihatil ka'batish sharīfati, Allāhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 3 units of Witr Wajib, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Isha</td><td>2 Rakat Nafl</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillāhi ta'ālā rak'atai salātil Ishā' nafli mutawajjihan ilā jihatil ka'batish sharīfati, Allāhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 2 units of Isha Nafl, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n",
