        "body": "\n                    <h4>What is Sawm?</h4>\n                    <p>Fasting from dawn (Fajr) to sunset (Maghrib), abstaining from food, drink, smoking, and marital relations. (Quran 2:183)</p>\n                    \n                    <h4>Niyyah (Intention) for Starting the Fast</h4>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-arabic\">نَوَيْتُ أَنْ أَصُومَ غَدًا مِنْ شَهْرِ رَمَضَانَ الْمُبَارَكِ فَرْضًا لِلَّهِ تَعَالَى</div>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-pronunciation\">🔊 Nawaytu an asuma ghadan min shahri ramadanal mubarak fardhan lillahi ta'ala</div>\n                    <p>\"I intend to fast tomorrow for the blessed month of Ramadan as an obligation for Allah, the Most High.\"</p>\n\n                    <h4>Dua for Iftar (Breaking the Fast)</h4>\n                    <h5>Common/Extended Dua:</h5>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-arabic\">اللَّهُمَّ إِنِّي لَكَ صُمْتُ وَبِكَ آمَنْتُ وَعَلَى رِزْقِكَ أَفْطَرْتُ بِرَحْمَتِكَ يَا أَرْحَمَ الرَّاحِمِينَ</div>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-pronunciation\">🔊 Allahumma inni laka sumtu, wa bika aamantu, wa 'ala rizqika aftartu, birahmatika ya Arhamar Raahimeen</div>\n                    <p>\"O Allah, for You I have fasted, in You I believe, and with Your provision I break my fast. By Your mercy, O Most Merciful of the merciful.\"</p>\n\n                    <h5>Sunnah Dua:</h5>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-arabic\">ذَهَبَ الظَّمَأُ وَابْتَلَّتِ الْعُرُوقُ وَثَبَتَ الْأَجْرُ إِنْ شَاءَ اللَّهُ</div>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-pronunciation\">🔊 Dhahaba adh-dhama'u wabtallatil-'uruqu wa thabatal-ajru in sha Allah</div>\n                    <p>\"The thirst has gone, the veins are moistened, and the reward is assured, if Allah wills.\" (Sunan Abi Dawud 2357)</p>\n\n                    <h4>Suhoor (Pre-Dawn Meal)</h4>\n                    <p>The Prophet ﷺ said: <em>\"Take suhoor, for indeed there is blessing in suhoor.\"</em> (Sahih Bukhari 1923 & Sahih Muslim 1095)</p>\n\n                    <h4>Who is Exempt?</h4>\n                    <p>(Based on Quran 2:184-185)</p>\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>The sick or on medication</li>\n                        <li>Travelers</li>\n                        <li>Pregnant, breastfeeding, or menstruating women</li>\n                        <li>The elderly who cannot fast</li>\n                        <li>Children before puberty</li>\n                    </ul>\n                ",
